review_text: Online customer service for Webster isn't very good. Things have changed quite a bit this last year.
we have been customers of webster bank going on 30 years. always helpful and there when we need them

My husband and I have had a terrible experience with the mortgage department at Webster bank!!! They are disorganized and don't answer or return phone calls... did not help guide us or prepare us for possible hiccups... very disappointed in the service provided. The pandemic is no excuse I am a nurse I show up to work everyday and provide the best care possible probably give better service since family members are unable to visit! I will never use them again I can not wait to build my house and use a different lender !

Beware of this bank
My wife went in to cash her paycheck and they gave her fake 20.00 bills 
She went back within minutes after learning bills were fake at chase next door  and declined to help her
What a joke this bank is!
She lost money now due to this 

Really???

Here we are, a month later... And another screw up - our statement this moth shows $125 fee for the first disbursement, despite our confirmation at the time of disbursement that there were ZERO fees associated with it and despite the fact that we prepaid for 4 disbursements at $150 each at closing. Can't wait to see what next month has in store...

I try to avoid this bank.  I am concerned about safety at this location.  I have more than once witnessed the teller inside asking out loud for a social security number!  This last time the bank manager did not seem bothered by this.  I suppose this is normal???  Then the teller followed this with the person's home address!!!!  The name was provided earlier.  Is this for real?  a bank that we think is protecting out life savings is giving away our identity?  i am now looking at the smaller credit unions.   i would like to know which banks have skilled tellers.  Another issue of concern at this bank as well as others is the lack of customer service set up with opportunity for privacy...office to discuss personal financial matters allow for security /privacy!  while we have more identity theft, banks are giving away more information.

We have banked here for several years after moving from Milford Bank.  The ATM deposit feature is outstanding.  Now there is phone app to deposit checks.  Love this!  Banking manager there has been very to me in trying to alleviate fees, etc.
They are convenient and easy to do business with. I have had good response with issues and service procedures. The online site is easy to navigate.
